# Context Files Location

**Workspace and AI context docs** (e.g. workspace structure, repo layout, contributor context) live in one place only:

## Rule

- **Directory:** `.cursor/context/`
- **Canonical path (repo-relative):** `.cursor/context/` (e.g. `WORKSPACE_STRUCTURE.md` → `.cursor/context/WORKSPACE_STRUCTURE.md`).
- **Same on both machines:** Use this structure on **Shadow PC** (e.g. `C:\Users\Shadow\code\swg-bg\.cursor\context\`) and on the **WSL build/test dev box** (e.g. `~/localswgserver/.cursor/context/`). The repo is shared; keep context files here so both environments stay in sync.

## Do

- Put new workspace-structure, repo-layout, or AI-context docs in `.cursor/context/`.
- Reference them as `.cursor/context/<filename>` in rules and READMEs.
- Commit context file changes as **dev env** on **Ender_CursorConfig** (after code; see bellum-gero.mdc).

## Don't

- Do not put context docs at repo root or in ad-hoc locations.
- Do not create a different context path on WSL; use `.cursor/context/` there too.

## Quick reference

| Item | Path |
|------|------|
| Workspace structure | `.cursor/context/WORKSPACE_STRUCTURE.md` |
| Other context docs | `.cursor/context/` (add new files here) |
| Index of rules, skills, context | `.cursor/README.md` |
